lipify
------------------------------------------
lipify connects to http://api.ipify.org to query your current IP address. Both
IPv4 and IPv6 is supported, for connecting to the ipify server and returning
your address.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.11.2-1
  libipify-devel-0.4-1bl1
  libipify1-0.4-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.31.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-6
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/troglobit/lipify

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/troglobit/lipify/archive/v0.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack lipify-0.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./lipify-0.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/lipify-0.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/lipify-0.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libipify1-0.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libipify-devel-0.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(lipify)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/lipify.README
  /usr/share/doc/lipify/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/lipify/README.md

(libipify1)
  /usr/bin/cygipify-1.dll

(libipify-devel)
  /usr/include/ipify.h
  /usr/lib/libipify.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/lipify.pc

------------------

